      <p>Next time I see quince in the produce section, I will buy some so I can try this recipe. It sounds and looks yummy.<br />
But what I really wanted to say is that you aren&#8217;t alone in liking the scent of automobile fuels. I grew up loving the smell coming from diesel engines (it was more the scent left in the air from trucks &amp; buses ahead of us, as diesel in liquid form doesn&#8217;t do it for me). I think it was because that diesel scent meant we were on the I-5 going somewhere more populated &amp; fun than our rural town, but who knows.</p>
    </div>

