    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I grew up in a house where quince trees grew by the side of the road; I remember the exact place where we used to pick them to make quince jelly, it has been, well 20 years. In Portugal quince jelly/jam is very popular and it&#8217;ll be hard to find a person who has never tried it, but I have never eaten it any other way!  </p>
<p>When we move to Portugal, after the summer, I hope to remember this recipe.</p>
