    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>A friend with a quince tree got me into a heavy homemade quince paste and Manchego cheese phase.  The paste sets up really firm and can be sliced into translucent golden slices and looks so pretty on the plate.  Such an ugly fruit on the outside that transforms so magically on the stovetop.  Thanks for the memory!</p>
