      <p>Quince? Love it! &#8211;as a child growing up in Peru we would eat it right off the shrub, that is when the flower by some miracle made it to fruit&#8211;because as naughty children we liked to pluck the flowers off the shrub and pull it apart, don&#8217;t know why we did this, it was just a thing we did while hanging out.  Peruvians also use it to make Mazamorra Morada y/o Chicha Morada&#8211;made with purple corn, pineapple and species. Delicious!</p>
