    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Keep the peel and core.  Add those bits to a slow cooker with water and sugar and after a day of cooking you end up with the MOST delicious liquid gold, quince jelly.  Drizzle it on ice cream, crumpets, scones, meat.  Absolute perfection.</p>
    </div>

