      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">CB</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2016/01/quince/#comment-44917"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-01-11T11:15:07-05:00">Monday, January 11, 2016 at 11:15 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have a three year old quince tree in my garden and it already produces an abundance of lovely big fruit.  I bake slices of quince in a sugar syrup with star aniseed or cinnamon in the oven on a low temperature for two hours or more. The rosy red colour is so beautiful and the house is perfumed.  Bliss!  I do find cutting and peeling quinces a bit of an ordeal but the end product makes it all worthwhile.  Now I shall check out all the links shown here.</p>
    </div>

